This article is about remarks made by President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump regarding Melania's dedication to the country and to children. Melania has visited hospitals, schools, and families affected by the opioid crisis. The President praises her sincerity, grace, and love, and states that her care and compassion for the nation's children inspire others. The President then signs the "Be Best Proclamation" and jokes about who will get the pen.